I carefully reviewed with the patient and her husband the natural history of rectal cancer.  I agree with the treatment as per our colleagues in 13090.  Mrs. Work has recovered from the recent chemotherapy and radiation therapy and is asymptomatic and fully active.  Although there is history of depression, this appears to be very well-controlled.  She was laughable, appropriate, in good spirits today.
Regarding the anterior chest pain, this did not have a cardiac source, neither appeared to be pulmonary embolism.  She had a Port-A-Cath in place for the chemotherapy administration.  I did not notice a check for DVT.  We may need to address this with Dr. Guidry from Colorectal Surgery.
Mrs. Work will see Dr. Guidry from Colorectal Surgery later.  The patient and her husband are aware that she is likely to receive further chemotherapy after surgery.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, but would like additional information. Advance Directive information packet provided to the patient. ID4144-05, UW9392-80, RL2029-19, KQ5854-33.

